import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    chart = sns.barplot(x='job', y='count', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job types in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Job Types', loc='upper right', labels=data['job'].unique())
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    sex_counts = data.groupby('sex')['count'].sum()
    plt.pie(sex_counts, labels=sex_counts.index, autopct='%.2f%%')
    plt.title('How does the count of males and females compare in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(sex_counts.index, title="Sex", loc="upper right")
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='count', data=data, ci=None)
    plt.title('What is the trend of count over the years in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.legend(title='Count', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    job_perc = data.groupby('job')['perc'].sum().reset_index()
    plt.pie(job_perc['perc'], labels=job_perc['job'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the percentage distribution of job types in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    pivot_data = data.pivot_table(index='year', columns='sex', values='count', aggfunc='sum').fillna(0)
    pivot_data = pivot_data.div(pivot_data.sum(1), axis=0)
    pivot_data.plot(kind='area', stacked=True, alpha=0.5)

    plt.title('How does the count of males and females vary over the years in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend(title='Sex', loc='upper left')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
